actions.comment:
Thanks for the detailed repro.

`SKFontManager.MatchTypeface` only searches fonts known to the system font manager — it cannot find custom fonts loaded via `SKTypeface.FromStream()` because those are not registered with any font manager. On Blazor WASM, the system font manager has no fonts at all, so `MatchTypeface` will always return null.

This method was marked `[Obsolete]` in SkiaSharp 2.x because it didn't work reliably across platforms, and it has been removed entirely in SkiaSharp 3.x.

Here's a workaround: load each font style variant as a separate embedded resource:

```csharp
var regular = SKTypeface.FromStream(assembly.GetManifestResourceStream("App.tahoma.ttf"));
var bold = SKTypeface.FromStream(assembly.GetManifestResourceStream("App.tahomabd.ttf"));
// Select the typeface directly based on desired style
```

If your font file contains multiple styles, you can still only access the default style via `FromStream`. Most font families ship Bold/Italic as separate `.ttf` files.
